key_trends: Increased focus on sustainability and reducing food waste
Growing adoption of AI and machine learning in retail
Demand for improved supply chain efficiency and resilience

competitive_vulnerabilities: Reliance on data quality and availability
Potential competition from larger, established players with broader offerings

growth_indicators: Forecast accuracy improvement over existing methods
growth_bottlenecks: Maintaining data quality and model accuracy as the customer base grows

key_risks: Inaccurate forecasts leading to customer dissatisfaction
Competition from established players or new entrants
Difficulty in acquiring and maintaining high-quality data

strengths: Strong value proposition in a large and growing market
Potential for significant ROI through waste reduction and increased sales
Experienced team with expertise in AI and retail
concerns: Dependence on data quality and model accuracy

next_steps: Focus on building strong relationships with key grocery retailers
Continuously improve the accuracy and reliability of the AI model
expansion_opportunities: Expand into adjacent markets such as restaurants or food distributors
Develop additional features such as inventory management or pricing optimization
